1. Ja sam kupio novi *harmoniku* jer sam se umorio od sviranja na staroj *harpici*. (I bought a new accordion because I got tired of playing on the old harmonica.)
2. Uvek sam se divio *harfistima* zbog njihove sposobnosti da stvore tako nežan zvuk. (I always admired harpists for their ability to create such a delicate sound.)
3. Bilo je to nezaboravno veče uz *harmoničare* koji su nas zabavljali do kasno u noć. (It was an unforgettable evening with the accordion players who entertained us until late at night.)
4. *Harfom* se najčešće sviraju romantične balade i melodije. (The harp is most commonly used to play romantic ballads and melodies.)
5. *Harpističino* majstorstvo na koncertu nas je sve ostavilo bez daha. (The harpist's mastery at the concert left us all breathless.)
6. Mladi *harmonikaš* se upravo priprema da svira na pozornici. (The young accordionist is getting ready to play on stage.)
7. *Harfom* se može stvoriti predivan zvuk koji opušta um i telo. (The harp can create a beautiful sound that relaxes the mind and body.)
8. Bio sam iznenađen kada sam video da moj prijatelj vešto svira na *harmoniki*. (I was surprised when I saw my friend skillfully playing the accordion.)
9. *Harpistkin* nastup je bio vrhunac večeri na muzičkom festivalu. (The harpist's performance was the highlight of the evening at the music festival.)
10. *Harmonikaši* su obično popularni na narodnim veseljima i svadbama. (Accordion players are usually popular at folk celebrations and weddings.)